==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lierne rib
<hw>Lierne" rib`</hw> <pr>(ly⟦acir⟧rn" r⟦icr⟧b`)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>lierne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>In Gothic
vaulting, any rib which does not spring from the impost and is not a
ridge rib, but passes from one boss or intersection of the principal
ribs to another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lieu</ent>⟦br⟧
